summary: Listen I know everyone paints Steve Rogers as a soldier à la Soldier Steve Rogers And Spy Natasha Romanoff, and yeah, by...
body: Listen I know everyone paints Steve Rogers as a soldier à la Soldier Steve Rogers And Spy Natasha Romanoff, and yeah, by definition, he is literally a (super)soldier. However, I was watching the first Avengers with my dad recently, and you know how there’s that whole the-team-argues-and-steve-is-like-“don’t-question-the-people-in-charge”-and-then-he-goes-and-questions-the-people-in-charge thing? My dad, an ex-military guy, goes, “That’s not what a real soldier would do. A soldier wouldn’t go investigate and question authority like that. Soldiers follow orders, no questions asked.” And yeah, of course. Of course a real authentic soldier would just follow orders; that’s the whole point. You need people to work efficiently, and that often means no questions can be asked or nothing will happen the way it’s supposed to. But that’s not who Steve Rogers is, and that’s not the point of Captain America. He doesn’t like bullies. He doesn’t like bullies, and that is of the utmost importance to him, isn’t it? So if he gets suspicious that the people he’s supposed to be taking orders from are actually the bullies, then darn right his morals are going to override whatever soldiers-follow-orders code he might stick to. And anyway, I was thinking, it’s not like Steve was ever really trained to be a soldier at all, was he? He did, what, a week of bootcamp to pick the subject for the serum experiment? No way is that enough time to beat Follow Orders into anyone. At the end of it, anyway, Erskine picked Steve specifically because he was more than just a soldier. And afterwards, he went into showbiz. He started doing soldier-y stuff on an impulse and he got away with it because he’s so staunchly a leader, never a follower. He’s a natural-born leader with no chill. Zero chill. He was never a soldier.

title: His Masterpiece
body:
read it on the AO3 at https://ift.tt/2Kg9APh

by rainbowsoldier

“You will know, James. It will be breathtaking, you won’t be able to stop looking at it or listening. You will discover something new about it every time. You have to feel it, understand it your way. You can’t follow someone else’s opinion. Everyone considers something else a masterpiece. And I’m pretty sure it’s something else for you. Everybody has their own.”
James Barnes was never interested in art.
And then it happened.
He felt as if something hit him in the head. Maybe it actually happened, Bucky wasn’t sure. What he did know was that he found his masterpiece. And Ms. Abbott was right, Steve Rogers was in fact breathtaking.
